leitmotifs
	n. a recurrent theme throughout a musical or literary composition
pecuniary
	adj. relating to or consisting of money
apocrypha
	n. writings or reports not considered genuine
salubrious
	adj. health-giving; healthy
proclivities
	n. a tendency to choose or do something regularly
surreptitious
	adj. kept secret, especially because it would not be approved of
gadfly
	n. an annoying person, especially one who provokes others into action by criticism
solicitous
	adj. characterized by or showing interest or concern
unconscionable
	adj. not right or reasonable
pidgins
	n. simplified form of a language, used for communication between people not sharing a common language